---
import HoverImage from './HoverImage';

const interests = [
  { text: 'technology', image: '/interests/technology.jpg' },
  { text: 'memes', image: '/interests/memes.jpg' },
  { text: 'sports', image: '/interests/sports.jpg' },
  { text: 'video games', image: '/interests/videogames.jpg' },
  { text: 'music', image: '/interests/music.jpg' },
];
---

<section class='max-w-4xl space-y-8 text-lg'>
  <p class='leading-relaxed'>
    i'm a software engineer currently in my third year studying computer science
    at bbu. i'm looking for opportunities to work with people who care about
    building things that matter.
  </p>

  <p class='leading-relaxed'>
    the <a
      href='/setup'
      class='text-foreground underline hover:text-accent-hover transition-colors'
      >tools</a
    > i reach for most of the time are react, tailwindcss, motion, and typescript.
    i <a
      href='/projects'
      class='text-foreground underline hover:text-accent-hover transition-colors'
      >build things</a
    > that cure my own icksâ€”smoothing out the rough edges i bump into in everyday
    apps.
  </p>

  <p class='leading-relaxed'>
    started programming because i wanted to take things apart and see how they
    actually work. it wasn't just about the syntax; it was about the way things
    fit together. that drive to understand the 'why' is still what keeps me
    building today.
  </p>

  <p class='leading-relaxed text-muted'>
    i like{' '}<span
      class='inline sm:inline-flex sm:flex-wrap sm:items-baseline'
      >{
        interests.map((item, index) => (
          <>
            <HoverImage
              client:load
              text={item.text}
              imageSrc={item.image}
              imageAlt={item.text}
            />
            <span class='hidden sm:inline'>
              {index < interests.length - 2
                ? ','
                : index === interests.length - 2
                  ? ', and'
                  : '.'}
            </span>
            <span class='sm:hidden -ml-1'>
              {index < interests.length - 2
                ? ', '
                : index === interests.length - 2
                  ? ', and '
                  : '.'}
            </span>
            {index < interests.length - 1 && (
              <span class='hidden sm:inline'>&nbsp;</span>
            )}
          </>
        ))
      }</span
    >
  </p>
</section>
